text: The Baojun E200 is a electric microcar made by SAIC-GM-Wuling under the Baojun brand since 2018. == History and Features == The Baojun E200 was launched in 2018 being avaliable to order at market launch in China in February of the same year the car is the second electric car from Baojun after the Baojun E100 the Baojun E200 has a electric motor of 29 kW (39 hp) and two versions with different ranges:a version with a range of 210 km (103 mi) and another version with a range of 270 km (167 mi). A rebadged version called Wuling Nano EV was launched at the Tianjin International Auto Show in 2021. this version has two editions based on the characters of the Zootopia movie. == Markets == The Baojun E200 alongside the Wuling Nano EV are currently sold mainly in the Chinese market. == References == Category:Chinese automobiles Category:2010s automobiles Category:2020s automobiles
title: Baojun E200
